shared_text:
Raymond Central High School Cheer Team
August 4 at 7:21 PM ¬∑

‚Ä¢ 2020 UCA HOME CAMP ‚Ä¢

Give a hand for all these athletes hard work & dedication to RCHS Cheer! Not only were they awarded as a team for ‚ÄúSuperior Stunting Performance‚Äù but they learned over 15 different stunts in 2 days!

Also another incredible opportunity was presented to the athletes that they could tryout for the UCA All American Team. They had 12 hours to learn a sideline dance, cheer, & jumps that then would be performed the next day at tryouts!

The All-American Team represents elite cheerleaders who represent USA cheerleaders worldwide. They also get the chance to cheer in London during the New Years Parade with cheerleaders all around the country!
Congratulations: Zoie Stachura, Ellianna LaMay, Grace Mueller, Ellie Hula, Megan Lange & Mallory Hughes for receiving 2020 UCA All American!

Many other awards were given throughout the camp that highlighted athletes performance & characteristics!

Awesome Job RCHS CHEER ATHLETES for giving 110% and we look forward to showing the community what we have been dedicating all our hard work and time on!
#MakinHistory2020

shared_text:
I Am A Rural Teacher
May 22 at 3:00 PM ¬∑

We are asking how COVID-19 is impacting rural communities. Read below how one Nebraska community solved the problem of having no formal ceremony to recognize their prom court. You can share yours here: http://buff.ly/3d7hWUe | Raymond Central High School | Nebraska Rural Community Schools Association

"On April 6th, Mr. Gralheer (Assistant Principal) and I drove around and crowned our Prom Royalty. We had online voting and once voting closed, we notified the parents of our winners and scheduled time to go over to their house to surprise them. The seniors had no idea. Our secretaries made signs and goodie bags for our winners."

See the video Raymond made about this event here on Facebook: https://buff.ly/3bQ38IB

Dear Raymond Central Community,

Please view the following attached invitation to our Discovery Education Community Kickoff Event.

This event will be held at the high school on Thursday, April 2nd, 2020 from 5pm-8pm.

There is a link in the invitation and at the bottom of this message to RSVP / Register for the event. We would like to know if you are planning on attending, and how many from your family will be there.

There will be refreshments served, so we would like to have a headcount for planning.

This is an exciting opportunity to hear about some great programs that are coming to Raymond Central and how it will impact learning in our schools. We are excited to partner with you in this adventure.

post_text: The University of Nebraska Extension has been contracted by the Department of Health and Human Services to conduct a community health analysis. Our aim is to gather information from residents of Saunders and surrounding counties, in an effort to uncover the barriers and challenges experienced in regards to accessing health care services. Of particular interest is diabetes management and education. Please use the link included at the bottom of the attached flyer or contact Nebraska Extension at 402.727.2775 to register for any and all community meetings. Your input is vitally important as we move forward in expanding and improving upon health services available in Saunders County.

This will be the first year for before- and after-school programs at Raymond Central, and will be Civic Nebraska‚Äôs eighth school-based youth civic leadership program in Nebraska.

Civic Nebraska will host an informational meeting at 7 p.m. on Tuesday, Feb. 4, in the Swing Classroom at Raymond Central High School, 1800 W. Agnew Road. Parents and families are welcome to attend.

Please see more information attached!

Below are the times and locations to meet your regular bus driver. We ask that your student ride with the same driver even though two buses may be in the same location to keep our rosters consistent.

Buses will still pickup students who live directly off a hard surface road. Please contact your bus driver with any questions.

LeAnn - Raymond @ 7:25 AM and Agnew 7:40 AM
Mr. B - Raymond @ 7:35 AM
PJ - Ceresco @ 7:35 AM
Becky - Ceresco @ 7:35 AM
Matt - Davey @ 7:25 AM
Rhonda - Valparaiso @ 7:45 AM

We will monitor the condition of gravel roads throughout the day tomorrow. It sounds like road crews will begin work tomorrow, however, we are not sure of the time it will take to get the roads in conditions safe for our buses.

Central Players High School Speech Team competed at Papillon LaVista for the first varsity tournament of the year. Receiving awards were:

Varsity Entertainment: Logan Parde 6th
Novice Extemp: Faith Johnson 5th
Varsity Extemporaneous:
5th Leany Enevoldsen
3rd Isaiah Enevoldsen
Varsity HI: 3rd. Hunter Kohl
Varsity Inform: 6th. Haley Hain
Varsity Poetry: 5th Grace Cadotte
Team: 5th

The team heads to Lincoln Pius X next week. Check out the team photos. Absent is Calleigh Osmera who had leave due to illness.

Allison Stansberry Nancy Vandenberg Osmera Carolyn M. Enevoldsen Kent Millington Harriet Gould
